    public class MorseCodeTree

      • translateFromMorseCode

        public java.lang.String translateFromMorseCode(java.lang.String morseCode)
                                        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Non-recursive method for translating a String comprised of morse code values through traversals in the MorseCodeTree. The given input is expected to contain morse code values, with '*' for dots and '-' for dashes, representing only letters in the English alphabet. This method will also handle exceptional cases, namely if a given token's length exceeds that of the tree's number of possible traversals, or if the given token contains a character that is neither '*' nor '-'.
        Parameters:
        morseCode - The given input representing letters in Morse code
        Returns:
        a String representing the decoded values from morseCode
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
